    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>GDG base entries are created via the IDCAMS <a href=\"https://www.ibm.com/docs/en/zos/3.2.0?topic=commands-define-generationdatagroup\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">DEFINE GENERATIONDATAGROUP</a> command.</p>\n<p>There is a section in the documentation on <a href=\"https://www.ibm.com/docs/en/zos/3.2.0?topic=commands-invoking-access-method-services-from-your-program\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">invoking IDCAMS from within your program</a>, but it seems to presume the invoking program is Assembler.</p>\n<p>In my experience, job step failure due to a GDG base being undefined is not something recovered from programmatically.  Implementation plans include define all required GDG base entries.</p>\n"
  }, {
